        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8590",
        "content": "Now this King was become a very old man, weakened and wasted with age and sickness and decrepitude; for he had lived an hundred and fourscore years and had no child, male or female, by reason whereof he was ever in cark and care from morning to night and from night to morn.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-normal",
